               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290409-304-person2797">
                  WILLIAM 
                  BENTON
               <interp inst="t18290409-304-person2797" type="surname" value="BENTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-304-person2797" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-304-person2797" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an <rs id="t18290409-304-viclabel1724" type="occupation">ironmonger</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290409-304-victim2796 t18290409-304-viclabel1724"></join>, and live in a court in Whitecross-street. On the 1st of April I went with these things to a public-house, to speak to a friend, and set my bundle on a cask by the side of the bar; I missed it in a minute; I went to the door, and a person said if any body has taken your bundle it is two women and a man, who are gone along <placeName id="t18290409-304-crimeloc1725">Beech-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18290409-304-crimeloc1725" type="placeName" value="Beech-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18290409-304-crimeloc1725" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290409-304-off1722 t18290409-304-crimeloc1725"></join>; we went along there, into the French Horn public-house, and saw the three prisoners there together; I said, "It is very strange my bundle is gone, and no one has been in the house but yourselves;" Brown and Lane said, "We have no bundle" - Hands said nothing; in about a minute and a half I saw my bundle under Hand's shawl; I said,"You are a bad woman, here is my bundle;" "Here is your bundle," said she.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290409-304-person2798">
                  JOHN 
                  AXE
               <interp inst="t18290409-304-person2798" type="surname" value="AXE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-304-person2798" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-304-person2798" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a shoemaker. I was in the King's Arms, and saw the three prisoners there; they had a quartern of gin; I did not see the bundle taken - I came out with them, and saw them go on towards the French Horn, in Beech-street; when the bundle was missed, I went in, and said it must have been taken by the two women and the man who had been leaning against the cask; I followed them into the French Horn, and asked if they had taken a bundle by mistake from the Cat, as it is called; they said they had not; but the prosecutor and the officer went in, and Hands gave it up.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290409-304-person2799">
                  JOSEPH 
                  ORTON
               <interp inst="t18290409-304-person2799" type="surname" value="ORTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-304-person2799" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-304-person2799" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was coming by, and went into the public-house; Hands said, "This is your bundle, take it;" I said I should take her into custody - "Brown said,"You have got your bundle, what more do you want;"<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182904090140"></xptr>on going to the Compter, Hands said Brown gave it her; he denied it - he was very much intoxicated.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290409-304-person2800">
                  THOMAS 
                  JONES
               <interp inst="t18290409-304-person2800" type="surname" value="JONES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-304-person2800" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-304-person2800" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I was sent for to assist to take the prisoners; Hands said that Brown took took the bundle, and brought it to the door; Brown said,"O you wicked woman, I never did such a thing.</p>
               <p>Hands put in a written defence, stating that Brown had given her the bundle to carry.</p>
               <p>HANDS - <rs id="t18290409-304-verdict1726" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18290409-304-verdict1726" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 36.</p>
